1
00:00:55,080 --> 00:00:57,010
Why did you suddenly come to see me?

2
00:00:57,440 --> 00:00:59,760
I haven't spent much time with you lately.

3
00:00:59,760 --> 00:01:02,560
Ding Shiyu said you've been under a lot of stress recently.

4
00:01:02,560 --> 00:01:04,680
So I wanted to take you out for a walk.

5
00:01:05,040 --> 00:01:07,970
That stinky fish Ding. Why does she blab everything?

6
00:01:11,200 --> 00:01:12,360
Who's talking behind my back?

7
00:01:12,360 --> 00:01:13,200
Stinky fish?

8
00:01:16,320 --> 00:01:17,120
It's nothing.

9
00:01:39,600 --> 00:01:40,729
Careful not to trip.

10
00:01:44,039 --> 00:01:44,960
Thank you.

11
00:01:47,840 --> 00:01:50,160
Look, the reefs over there are so pretty.

12
00:01:56,640 --> 00:01:58,600
Oh no, my phone is dead.

13
00:01:59,160 --> 00:02:01,420
Can I borrow your phone to take a picture?

14
00:02:02,560 --> 00:02:03,220
Here you go.

15
00:02:15,240 --> 00:02:16,240
I'm so good.

16
00:02:16,400 --> 00:02:18,060
The picture turned out great.

17
00:02:24,720 --> 00:02:25,880
Brother Tianyu.

18
00:02:28,480 --> 00:02:30,320
So you are Ye Tianyu.

19
00:02:32,560 --> 00:02:34,160
My childhood friend.

20
00:02:35,520 --> 00:02:36,720
Ye Tianyu.

21
00:02:42,280 --> 00:02:43,079
What's wrong?

22
00:02:44,240 --> 00:02:46,480
You used to be a race car driver?

23
00:02:52,800 --> 00:02:54,130
That was many years ago.

24
00:02:54,920 --> 00:02:57,920
My dad was a racing coach back then.

25
00:02:59,800 --> 00:03:01,660
He later trained me to be a driver.

26
00:03:03,400 --> 00:03:05,730
We even won many national championships.

27
00:03:05,840 --> 00:03:07,280
When was that?

28
00:03:07,880 --> 00:03:09,400
Why did you stop racing?

29
00:03:11,920 --> 00:03:12,840
And then...

30
00:03:14,640 --> 00:03:16,600
My mom passed away in an accident.

31
00:03:18,760 --> 00:03:20,760
And things became what they are now.

32
00:03:23,560 --> 00:03:24,520
I'm sorry.

33
00:03:27,680 --> 00:03:28,810
It's all in the past.

34
00:03:44,920 --> 00:03:45,960
Are you Liu Yaqi?

35
00:03:46,200 --> 00:03:46,560
Yes.

36
00:03:46,880 --> 00:03:48,120
Our chairman will see you

37
00:03:48,120 --> 00:03:49,560
at the hotel at 2:00 PM today.

38
00:03:49,560 --> 00:03:51,320
Okay, see you later.

39
00:04:05,880 --> 00:04:07,080
Hello, Mr. Dong.

40
00:04:07,360 --> 00:04:09,220
Liu Yaqi is coming to see me later.

41
00:04:09,480 --> 00:04:10,680
He's looking for you?

42
00:04:10,880 --> 00:04:11,880
He didn't tell me.

43
00:04:12,760 --> 00:04:13,920
Okay, I got it.

44
00:04:16,360 --> 00:04:17,089
I'm leaving.

45
00:04:19,160 --> 00:04:20,290
Where are you going?

46
00:04:20,360 --> 00:04:21,620
I have something to do.

47
00:04:38,760 --> 00:04:39,360
Mr. Dong.

48
00:04:40,159 --> 00:04:40,800
I know.

49
00:04:41,480 --> 00:04:42,680
You invited me today,

50
00:04:43,360 --> 00:04:45,420
which is already doing me a big favor.

51
00:04:45,720 --> 00:04:46,320
I am sorry.

52
00:04:47,000 --> 00:04:49,000
I was foolish recently.

53
00:04:49,520 --> 00:04:51,920
I have no right to beg for your forgiveness.

54
00:04:52,480 --> 00:04:53,610
But I came here today

55
00:04:54,040 --> 00:04:54,920
just to beg you.

56
00:04:56,520 --> 00:04:59,000
As long as it makes the factory's business better,

57
00:04:59,000 --> 00:05:00,530
I am willing to do anything.

58
00:05:11,600 --> 00:05:12,860
I offer you this toast.

59
00:05:29,760 --> 00:05:30,320
Here.

60
00:05:44,040 --> 00:05:45,100
What are you doing?

61
00:05:45,240 --> 00:05:45,880
Stand up.

62
00:05:46,200 --> 00:05:47,240
Stand up.

63
00:05:52,120 --> 00:05:54,580
Do you know how much weight your words carry?

64
00:05:55,360 --> 00:05:57,220
Saying you'll do anything for me.

65
00:05:58,360 --> 00:05:59,360
If I make you work for the rest of your life

66
00:05:59,360 --> 00:06:01,480
as my auto mechanic for free,

67
00:06:01,600 --> 00:06:02,720
would you agree to that?

68
00:06:02,720 --> 00:06:03,780
I would be willing.

69
00:06:07,240 --> 00:06:08,900
A man's knees are made of gold.

70
00:06:09,280 --> 00:06:10,810
Don't just kneel to anyone.

71
00:06:11,840 --> 00:06:14,040
I know I shouldn't just kneel to anyone,

72
00:06:16,240 --> 00:06:17,640
but this is for my family.

73
00:06:46,000 --> 00:06:46,659
Have a seat.

74
00:06:49,960 --> 00:06:51,820
How about it? Can you still drink?

75
00:06:52,920 --> 00:06:53,840
I'm fine.

76
00:06:54,840 --> 00:06:55,440
Let me.

77
00:06:56,800 --> 00:06:57,600
You know what?

78
00:06:58,600 --> 00:07:00,200
You are the same age as my son.

79
00:07:01,200 --> 00:07:02,720
Just as unwilling to admit defeat,

80
00:07:02,720 --> 00:07:03,850
never backing down.

81
00:07:06,560 --> 00:07:07,490
I don't know him,

82
00:07:08,360 --> 00:07:09,690
nor do I understand him.

83
00:07:10,640 --> 00:07:11,080
I don't understand

84
00:07:11,080 --> 00:07:13,140
why his family gives him so much help.

85
00:07:14,840 --> 00:07:16,570
But he just wouldn't accept it.

86
00:07:16,880 --> 00:07:19,760
Is it because when he was little,

87
00:07:20,480 --> 00:07:22,210
I spent too little time with him

88
00:07:23,160 --> 00:07:25,290
and communicated too little with him?

89
00:07:25,880 --> 00:07:27,680
I didn't understand him before.

90
00:07:29,320 --> 00:07:30,880
But seeing you today,

91
00:07:32,240 --> 00:07:33,370
I think I get him now,

92
00:07:34,840 --> 00:07:35,970
and understand him.

93
00:07:38,040 --> 00:07:38,680
Come on,

94
00:07:39,280 --> 00:07:39,960
young man.

95
00:07:40,640 --> 00:07:42,040
I toast this glass to you.

96
00:07:50,000 --> 00:07:52,530
I don't want any of these guarantees from you.

97
00:07:52,920 --> 00:07:54,250
I am willing to help you.

98
00:07:55,640 --> 00:07:56,700
I helped, I helped.

99
00:07:57,720 --> 00:07:58,360
Who is it?

100
00:08:00,800 --> 00:08:02,240
Boss Dong, I'll go take a look.

101
00:08:02,240 --> 00:08:02,760
Okay.

102
00:08:15,240 --> 00:08:16,520
Su Wan, Su Wan.

103
00:08:16,880 --> 00:08:18,080
How are you? Are you okay?

104
00:08:18,080 --> 00:08:18,920
My leg.

105
00:08:21,880 --> 00:08:23,210
Hurry, Yaqi, call a car.

106
00:08:24,360 --> 00:08:24,840
Okay.

107
00:08:38,440 --> 00:08:39,520
At this moment,

108
00:08:40,159 --> 00:08:40,880
I know

109
00:08:41,960 --> 00:08:43,120
from now on,

110
00:08:44,159 --> 00:08:45,890
everything will be different.

111
00:08:46,880 --> 00:08:50,400
The feelings I fear to have but avoid talking about.

112
00:08:51,200 --> 00:08:53,200
And my fear of intimacy,

113
00:08:54,720 --> 00:08:56,720
because of the person in front of me,

114
00:08:57,280 --> 00:08:58,640
has vanished.
